Back in the old days, NESTICLE was cool, why? <br />because you could pause the emulation, bring up the on screen sprites, and then EDIT sprites and whatnot on the fly...<br />it also gave you the character address, this is what people used to make tables (.tbl) to use as a way to edit game text.<br />also how most people were able to make hack and make translation<br /><br />then snowbro came out with TLP and then a few years later TM, and so on...<br /><br />anyway where am i going with this... oh yes<br /><br />i want to get NESTICLE to work on my Win 7 64bit comp, any one know how?<br /><br />OR<br /><br />help me get out of the past and recommend a comparable program or editor that can edit on the fly, meaning while you are playing it...<br /><br /><br />btw im 77<br />i was around in the early days... 1998ish<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6545">x77x</a> — Mon Jun 02, 2014 7:31 pm</p><hr />
